      "purpose": "This paragraph closes the output files, OPFILE1 and OPFILE2. It displays a message indicating that the files are being closed. It checks the status of each CLOSE operation (WS-OUTFL1-STATUS and WS-OUTFL2-STATUS). If an error occurs during the close operation (status is not spaces or '00'), an error message is displayed, but the program does not abend. It consumes no input files but closes output files. It writes messages to the console using DISPLAY.",
